SLC()                                                                    SLC()

NNAAMMEE
       ssllcc - Utility for StrongNode development

       Utility for StrongNode development.

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       slc [options] [command] [args]
       slc <npm-command> [npm-command-args]
       slc <script-file> [args]

       Note that the second and third command forms are short forms of the npm
       and run commands described below. An unrecognized slc command  that  is
       an  npm  command  will be passed to npm, any other unrecognized command
       will be passed to the run command.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh, ----hheellpp
              print usage information

CCOOMMMMAANNDDSS
       nnppmm::   run a npm command

       rruunn::   run a node script

       eennvv::   print node environment information

       vveerrssiioonn::
              print node version

       hheellpp::  print usage information for a command

       ddeebbuugg:: debug a script

       ccrreeaattee::
              create node script boilerplate

       llbb::    create LoopBack workspaces, applications, and models

       eexxaammppllee::
              create example applications

EEXXAAMMPPLLEESS
           $ slc create web mywebapp
           $ slc run app.js
           $ slc npm list
           $ slc npm install -f express
           $ slc install -f express
           $ slc example chat my-chat

